LogFile.FinalText: Some would claim that men and women speak different languages. If the man in a partnership says that he doesn't want to discuss his problems, the typical woman would feel that she's excluded from his world. If the woman tells him that she doesn't want to discuss problems, most men would believe that she doesn't need to talk about them. These misunderstandings cause quarrels. When serious quarrels arise, women and men also react differently. Recent research indicates that many women cry when they are angry. Sometimes men choose to go away and they may feel helpless. In contrast to the crying woman, an angry man uses harsh words. In spite of different patterns of reaction, most men and women manage to live peacefully together, and we would probably not be able to live without each other.
